      "raw_text": "Authority for the statement pub\nlished in The Spokane Press last\nnight that there was rot union\nengineer employed in the Granite\nbuilding was a prominent member\nO. the engineers union. The state\nment was found to be incorrect to-\nday.\n\n\nAlthough he has recently employ\ned a union engineer at the Granite\nbuilding, Edward O'Shea, whose\nname is now before the city coun-\nGil as candidate to succeed F. e.\nWeymouth, has not signed up with\nthe engineers union and is regarded\nas a nonunion man and an advocate\nof the open shop principle. James\nw, eller is the engineer employed\nat the Granite building."
